<br>
1) Some crafted item costs 100 plat to make.<br>
2) Tradeskiller A thinks 1000 is a fair price, since no one else can make it and only high end people need it.<br>
3) Tradeskiller B comes along, and thinks 150 platinum is a fair price.<br>
<br>
I'm talking about....<br>
<br>
1) Some crafted item costs 100 plat to make.<br>
2) Tradeskiller A thinks 150 plat is a fair price.<br>
3) Tradeskiller B also thinks 150 plat is a fair price, but he notices Tradeskiller A is also selling them for 150 plat, so Tradeskiller B charges 140 plat instead so he can monopolize the market.<br>
4) Things go downhill from there.<br>
<br>
I am not at all talking about price fixing, or somehow rigging the economy, or anything.  All I'm saying is that when tradeskillers start charging <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> less</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> than what they themselves think is the <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> fair</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> price, <!--EZCODE UNDERLINE START--><u>only</u><!--EZCODE UNDERLINE END--> so they can get a larger market share than someone else, it fucks up the tradeskill economy.<br>
<br>
And it doesn't benefit the server because people who enjoy tradeskills, the people who would actually enjoy GMing their skill and selling crap to you, can't get there because they can't fund their advancement through the sale of their goods because some ridiculous price war is going on.<br>
<br>
I'm not talking about people getting their ass kicked for charging 1000% profit so they can spend the money they got for GMing smithing first on velium swiftblades and ToV loot.  I'm talking about people who are trying to be professional tradeskillers being forced to adventure instead because the market is fucked to all hell by some ass trying to horde all the sales to him/herself.<br>
<br>
If Jarkell is selling a 100 plat cost item for 2,500 plat, and someone else comes along and charges 200 plat instead, more power to them.  Thank God.  Etc!<br>
<br>
But if someone is selling a 100 plat cost item for 120 plat, and some prick comes along and charges 110 plat instead so they can get all the sales (when they wouldn't have done so otherwise) they suck <!--EZCODE EMOTICON START :p --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/tongue.gif ALT=":p"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END--> <br>
