<br>
1)  Golden Tunare Idols, currently selling at 1500pp.  Average inter server price... 3kpp.  Admittedly the average inter server price on Iron Oxides is 1kpp, and the few potters on this server have kept that down, thus lowering prices.  None the less, the total cost of the PotC items on Firiona Vie from potters is noticeably less than the price elsewhere.<br>
<br>
2)  Opal Steins.  Yeah, they cost about 40-50pp to make.  They save the buyer 1kpp and more.  And yet people whine that 250pp is too much?  Excuse me?  Potter makes 200pp, you make thousands, and yer whining about that?  I mean, I use one Opal Stein (with my other gear I can soft cap Charisma with just one) and it saves me 200pp every time I purchase a new load of Star Rubys for tradeskilling.  200pp per purchase.  That one Opal Stein has saved me thousands of platinum in pottery goods alone (the savings everytime I buy the two stacks of saphires necessary to work on gate stones is enourmous).  If I had bought that item, as a dropped item, for 1kpp, thus giving the seller 1kpp, I still would have come out way ahead.  I certainly don't begrudge the tinker that charged me 1600pp for my gearlock smithing hammer... sure, she gained maybe 1kpp on the deal, but I saved more than that in not needing to gain the additional 10 skill points.<br>
<br>
Ya see, the way I see it is this.  If I'm tradeskilling away, I could be using that time to hunt.  Maybe killing cyclopses in OOT.  Maybe Sebilis.  Maybe some other place.  I could be gaining both exp and loot.  Thus, for it to be worth my time to tradeskill, I should be able to make more cash per unit time than I could running around looking for a group, finding one, and playing a while... to make up for the fact that I'm not getting exp.  So yeah, I should make decent money at tradeskilling... I'm doing a service, and getting paid for it.  I'm not sure why people think there's some certain amount of profit I have to get when I make the items... I price my items based on usefulness to the buyer.  This means some items I don't make... they just won't pay me enough, if I charge the buyer what it's worth to them.  I don't make Periodot Steins, for example.  <br>
<br>
And don't get me started on the concept that all items MUST be priced at twice their construction cost.  That's downright silly.  I've I'd priced my first Gatestones at twice cost to make, they would have been 16kpp each, and Star Ruby Steins would have been about 3700pp each (my first batch were 7k for 4).  But I knew the items weren't worth that to a buyer, so I didn't charge that much.  As my skill improved, I succeeded more, and the cost for me to make em got better... but that didn't improve or weaken the product in any way.  So Star Ruby Steins started at 2kpp each, because that was the inter server average at the time and it seemed reasonable, even though I made perhaps 250pp per stein sold and risked far more than that.  And gate stones were 10k, also the average at the time.  I didn't think that the Golden Diety Idol inter server average sounded right... they were running at 4kpp to 5kpp, but that just wasn't what I thought buyers should pay, considering the price of a Grodan's and Gorganga Idol.  So I said they were worth 1500pp... even though non Tunare Idols averaged 1350pp each at the time I set that price.  And when I priced Opal Steins... they were selling for 1kpp on other servers.  My skill went up, but I wasn't about to lower my price when I couldn't keep the darn things in stock... I'd make a batch of twenty, sell it out, make a new batch, and go hunting... people would send me tells for the things, and I'd ask them to come to me... and they would.  Tons of them.  And bought out whole batches in a night's hunting.  So yeah, I was selling for 250pp, and it was well worth it, as evidenced by the many people who sent me tells later saying how it had saved them so much money.<br>
<br>
So instead of saying an item should sell for an amount based on the making price, let's talk about what things should sell for based on value to the buyer.  <br>
<br>
Opal Steins:  25 charisma 10 mana.  Most charisma you can get on a primary or secondary item outside NToV and the GM tools.  Without knowing cost to make, what would this cost?  I doubt before the tradeskill patch anyone would have said less than 500pp.  I know that since they sold for 1kpp to enchanters when they first came out... and the enchanters were buying them in droves.  Except on Firiona Vie, were they never cost that much.  Now they sell for 50 to 100pp, though most folks who were making them stopped when the price bottomed out to as little as 25pp each.<br>
<br>
Star Ruby Steins:  20 mana 10 to all saves 5 charisma.  With blue diamond costs skyrocketing, resist gear ain't so cheap.  With two slots you can get 20 to all resists... admittedly these are slots you can put good things in, but that's still great caster resist gear, and helps you get an earing that's amazingly powerful for it's low price.  If that were a dropped item, how much would it sell for?  I know HQ Kodiak Pelts run 500 to 1kpp, and they're a very small part of a decent ring that even after a lot of work isn't as good as the Earing of the Solcetice.  And they don't have any effects in and of themselves.<br>
<br>
Golden Idol of Rallos Zek:  10 ac 9 str 5 sta 20 hp.  Range slot.  Tons of hitpoints for a warrior, plus great AC. What would that run at, if not made by a tradeskill?  Though admittedly these sell out as fast as I can make em, which is slow.<br>
<br>
Gatestones.  Unlimited charges gate to home city.  Pretty darned cool.  Yet I had people jumping me for charging 10k... when the first ones I made cost me as much as 8k each.  Sure, I should have waited to make them later, but I had people saying they wanted em.  So I made em, then had people after me for price gouging.  Ugh.  Took the price down as I skilled up, and still had people saying I was charging too much.  UGH!<br>
<br>
And of course Crucibles.  Damn.  Unlimited charges of evac... if it were a rare dropped item I imagine people would be quite happy.  But these are selling for 395pp each now.  By the way they cost maybe 70pp to make... but require fishing in Sebilis, making a 170 skill fishing combine, a high skill baking combine, farming greenies for a long time in the Gorge of King Xorb, and buying unstackable items in Surefall.  Right, I want to spend a few hours to make that much.  No!  If I'm in Sebilis, I'd rather kill some froggies, thank you much!<br>
<br>
Oh well, just had to get that off my chest.<br>
<br>
But to the original poster... don't kill the prices for everyone just because someone pisses you off.  Just flame the person and be done with it.  You start a huge price war, you hurt all the makers... then the buyers expect those prices always, and everyone leaves the buisiness, and no one's making the items anymore, and it's just pesky.  Just flame to get your aggressions out!<br>
<br>
Besides, I want some Constitutionals on the market.  I haven't seen any!  And all this ranting has made my throat itch.<br>
<br>
Jarkell Ravensteel <p></p><i></i></td></tr><tr bgcolor=d1c3b5><td nowrap width=20% valign=top align=left><span class=title> <A HREF=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ubjond.showPublicProfile?language=EN>Bjond</A>&nbsp; <IMG HEIGHT=10 WIDTH=10 SRC="http://www.ezboard.com/ezgfx/gicons/white_redspot.gif" BORDER=0></span><br> <span class=usertitle>Registered User</span><br> <font color=#A62A2A>(9/13/02 1:52 am)</font><br>   <a href=http://pub94.ezboard.com/ffirionaviefrm49.showAddReplyScreenFromWeb?topicID=16.topic&index=32>Reply</a>   </td><td valign=top align=left class=m><span class=title> Jar ..</span><hr size=1> .. I don't think you should be one to comment on how nice and reasonable your prices are.  After playing on several servers, IMHO, I can say you have some of the most inflated prices anywhere.  For instance, I noticed you selling fire opal wedding rings for 1500.  These are easy to make and typically run 450-500p including a 50% markup after failures.<br>
