3) Getting to the Plane of Growth typically requires passing Wuoshi so you have to work up you Claws of Veeshan faction.  You also have to be able to survive the Plane which means no evils.<br>
4) Getting out if the Plane of Growth requires Gate so the main foraging class requires a Thurgadin gate potion to gather any wood.<br>
5) Typical forage rate on Branch of Planar Oak with a 200 forage skill AND a foragers sickle (don't get me started on ow long and difficult that quest is) is about 2.5 per HOUR of sitting and hitting the forage key every 90 seconds.  That's a lot of fun!<br>
6) Blessed Emeralds can only be obtained from a Tunare worshipping Druid or Cleric.<br>
7) Making Celestial essence is another fairly long trip for non-porting classes.<br>
<!--EZCODE EMOTICON START 8) --><img src=http://www.ezboard.com/intl/aenglish/images/emoticons/glasses.gif ALT="8)"><!--EZCODE EMOTICON END-->  Add a trip to Thurgadin for the sacred coldain thread.<br>
9) Dragon Eggs require going to Western Wastes, which requires a trip through Siren's Grotto!<br>
10) Plus a tailoring combine with a trivial of 150, a Brewing combine with a trivial of 150 and a pottery combine with a trivial of 103 (don't forget 5% failure rate regardless of skill).<br>
<br>
Add all that up and you think 1500 is too much?  How about adding in that it is one of the most difficult of the nine items required to make an earring worth over 20,000 pp?<br>
<br>
60 minutes...that's nuts.  I spent 9 hours in PoG getting oak, weeks working up tailoring and fishing, days working up pottery.  And the fact is I STILL can't make poles because I can't get the components I need<br>
<br>
I got mobbed by light blue mobs in crystal Caverns trying to get a bit of velium and died with only a 50% rez.  Where does that factor into your calculations?  I've neer known anyone to die due to jewelcraft except at the very high end.<br>
<br>
So, if you think the mark-ups are too high try walking into a McDonalds and telling them their prices are too high because the cost to make their food is really low.<br>
